# Agent Instructions

This project is a .NET transactional integration job built on the Intropy
framework. It reads files from a local Dapr file binding, publishes each one
onto an in-memory Dapr pub/sub topic, and processes them through a VETER send
pipeline that writes the transformed result to a second local file binding.

## Project overview

- Framework: .NET 10
- App type: Console job (no web endpoints)
- Runner: `Intropy.Framework.Hosting.TransactionalIntegration.Job.TransactionalIntegrationRunner`
- Pub/sub component: `pubsub` (in-memory)
- Topic: `orders`
- Source binding: `inbound-storage` (Dapr local storage, rootPath `/tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/inbound`)
- Destination binding: `outbound-storage` (Dapr local storage, rootPath `/tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/outbound`)

## Important files

- `src/Program.cs` - DI wiring and entrypoint that runs the `TransactionalIntegrationRunner`.
- `src/Configuration/Constants.cs` - component names, keyed-adapter keys, context metadata keys.
- `src/Receive/` - source listing and the receive pipeline steps (`Receiver`, `Enqueuer`, `Completer`).
- `src/Send/` - the VETER send pipeline steps.
- `local/dapr-components/pubsub.yaml` - in-memory pub/sub component.
- `local/dapr-components/inbound-storage.yaml` / `outbound-storage.yaml` - Dapr local storage bindings.
- `local/sample-data/sample-order.json` - sample input to drop into the inbound folder.

## Development notes

- Source and destination `IFileAdapter` instances are registered as keyed singletons
  (`Constants.SourceFileAdapterKey`, `Constants.DestinationFileAdapterKey`). Inject them
  via `[FromKeyedServices(...)]` or resolve via `GetRequiredKeyedService<IFileAdapter>(...)`.
- The receive pipeline runs once per file returned by `ISourceLister`; the send
  pipeline runs once per pub/sub delivery.
- Keep `Constants.PubSubName` / `Constants.TopicName` in sync between
  `Program.cs` (`AddTransactionalIntegration`) and the Dapr component YAML.
- The send pipeline does not use idempotency or business-incident services in this
  sample - it is deliberately minimal. Add `.WithIdempotency(...)` and
  `.WithBusinessIncidents(...)` to the builder in `Send/ServiceCollectionExtensions.cs`
  once those services are reachable.

## Build and run

Build:

```bash
dotnet build ./src
```

Run with Dapr:

```bash
mkdir -p /tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/inbound /tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/outbound
cp local/sample-data/sample-order.json /tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/inbound/

dapr run \
  --app-id {{ .appId }} \
  --dapr-http-port 3500 \
  --resources-path ./local/dapr-components \
  -- dotnet run --project ./src
```
